properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 6 at 2:23PM PST until January 7 at 9:00AM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of northeast winds through early evening of 20 to
30 mph with gusts to 50 mph. For late tonight into Tuesday
morning, more localized northeast winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts
to 35 mph.

* WHERE...San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland
Empire, Riverside County Mountains, Santa Ana Mountains and
Foothills, San Diego County Mountains and San Gorgonio Pass
Near Banning.

* WHEN...Until 9 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The higher winds from earlier today have
weakened somewhat, but locally gusty winds will continue
through and below passes and canyons and along some of the
western foothills as late as early Tuesday morning.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM PST TUESDAY... ...HIGH WIND WARNING IS CANCELLED
